\section*{Cultural Variations in Privacy Norms}

Cultural norms and expectations regarding privacy vary across different regions, influenced by factors such as history, religion, and social structure. For instance, in collectivist societies, privacy is often viewed as a shared concept, with individuals prioritizing group interests over individual rights. In contrast, individualist societies tend to emphasize personal autonomy and the sanctity of private life.

